=== Float Formatting (the %g spec — docs/semantics.md) ===

Floats stringify via C's %g with precision 6, on every backend.
Two variants:
  - show / string_of_float / interpolation: bare %g           (3.0 -> "3")
  - display (final values, print, nested in structures): %g
    plus a trailing "." when the result could otherwise be
    read as an int; inf/nan are unambiguous so no dot          (3.0 -> "3.")

--- test: whole float displays with trailing dot
3.0
--- expect: 3.

--- test: show whole float has no trailing dot
show 3.0
--- expect: 3

--- test: string_of_float whole float has no trailing dot
string_of_float 100.0
--- expect: 100

--- test: string_of_float fractional
string_of_float 2.5
--- expect: 2.5

--- test: string interpolation of whole float
$"{2.0}"
--- expect: 2

--- test: string interpolation of fractional float
$"x = {1.25}"
--- expect: x = 1.25

--- test: float display rounds to six significant digits
123456.789
--- expect: 123457.

--- test: large float displays in scientific notation
1780344245.513
--- expect: 1.78034e+09

--- test: show large float scientific notation
show 1780344245.513
--- expect: 1.78034e+09

--- test: small float scientific notation
0.0000123
--- expect: 1.23e-05

--- test: boundary just below scientific threshold
0.0001
--- expect: 0.0001

--- test: ten billion collapses to one significant digit
10000000000.0
--- expect: 1e+10

--- test: negative large float
0.0 - 1234567.89
--- expect: -1.23457e+06

--- test: float infinity displays bare
1.0 / 0.0
--- expect: inf

--- test: float negative infinity displays bare
0.0 - 1.0 / 0.0
--- expect: -inf

--- test: show of float list uses bare float format
show [3.0; 100.0]
--- expect: [3; 100]

--- test: show of float tuple uses bare float format
show (1.5, 2.0)
--- expect: (1.5, 2)

--- test: float list with decimals displays unchanged
[1.5; 2.25]
--- expect: [1.5; 2.25]

--- test: string_of_float as first-class function
List.map string_of_float [1.5; 2.0]
--- expect: [1.5; 2]

--- test: string_of_bool as direct call
string_of_bool true
--- expect: true

--- test: print of float list uses display format
print [3.0; 100.0];;
()
--- expect: [3.; 100.]

--- test: whole float nested in tuple display
(1.5, 2.0)
--- expect: (1.5, 2.)

--- test: whole float nested in list display
[3.0; 100.0]
--- expect: [3.; 100.]

=== Nested Float Display Tests (BUG-3 regression suite) ===

--- test: whole float in map value display
print #{"a": 2.0};;
()
--- expect: [(a, 2.)]

--- test: whole float in option payload display
print (Some 4.0);;
()
--- expect: Some 4.

--- test: whole float in array display
print #[1.0; 2.5];;
()
--- expect: #[1.; 2.5]

--- test: whole float in record field display
print { alpha = 3.0; beta = "p" };;
()
--- expect: { alpha = 3.; beta = p }

--- test: whole float in nested list of tuples display
print [(1.0, 2); (3.5, 4)];;
()
--- expect: [(1., 2); (3.5, 4)]

--- test: show of nested whole float stays bare
show [3.0; 100.0]
--- expect: [3; 100]

--- test: float list as final value uses display format
[7.0; 8.25]
--- expect: [7.; 8.25]

--- test: variant with float payload as final value
type wrapped = Wrap of float | Empty
Wrap 5.0
--- expect: Wrap 5.

--- test: first-class print falls back to heuristic display
List.iter print [1.5; 2.25];;
()
--- expect: "1.5\n2.25"
